How are conflict-affected sunflower crops in Ukraine related to the price of chips locally? Well because of cooking oil, which is partly produced from those crops. Ukraine accounted for 40% of global exports of sunflower oil in 2020, while Russia accounted for 18%. #eNCA speaks to Morné Botes, Commercial Director of Southern Oil, which owns the B-Well and African Gold oil brands. #eNCA #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - The price of cooking oil is expected to surge. The conflict between Russia and Ukraine is contributing to the already ballooning price of sunflower oil in South Africa. READ: Rising food prices shake North Africa as Ukraine war rages The current supply pressures will also have an impact on the availability of the product. Ukraine accounted for 40 percent of global exports of sunflower oil in 2020, while Russia accounted for 18 percent.